  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f35a0dfaf3b168e49bbe856c5055efe5, type: 3}
  m_Name: TheCrow
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPCDialogue
  dialogueLines:
  - Caw! Caw caw! ca- *cough cough*
  - Apologies. It has been awhile since I have spoken to a human.
  - You have traveled through the villages of my kingdom, and now you find yourself
    in my castle.
  - ..yes this used to be a castle, I know....
  - You have seen the state of the villages, yes?
  - They used to be bustling with life.
  - They stand as they are now due to my own shortcomings.
  - 'A long, long time ago now, a wizard came to this kingdom. '
  - They saw how corrupt and greedy I was and how disjoint the villages of my kingdom
    were.
  - They turned me into a crow, locked away all the food into my castle, and gave
    a key to each village.
  - ..unfortunately, none of the villages could come together and unlock the tower,
    so they starved to death.
  - Take this kingdom as a warning, and lead your life with grace and kindness, rather
    than cruelty and regret.
  - Do not let your own homes devolve into chaos.
  - Be humble and recognize your faults - lest you get turned into a crow too.
  - Cursed to be seen as a symbol of death and watch only from above.
  - See, I had to watch as my kingdom crumbled away.
  - It used to be magnificient!
  - I held feasts ALL the time.
  - Drank the best wine!
  - Went hunting frequently. Obviously I'd get bears and such.
  - Oh and my steed, the most magnificient, tall horse a king could ask fo-
  - Oh. Right. Ahem.
  - Well. I'll be off now. Can't stick around this place anymore.
  autoProgressLines: 0101010101010101010101010101010101010101010101
  autoProgressDelay: 1.5
  typingSpeed: 0.05
